		<hr size="1">There isn't a race that's obviously better.</P><P>Both have advantages the other doesn't.  But both have disadvantages as well.</P><P>There is Vah Shir newbie armor, but it's not along the same lines as the Half-elf quests.  You might find, since you're not going to twink, that the Half-elf quests are better for you.  Personally, I find the wood-elf best, but that's just me.  The added forage is even better, and is in fact the reason I picked wood-elf.</P><P>Just remember, main stats to look at are CHA and DEX.  Between the two, HEF and VAH, I would pick HEF because of the better starting stats.  In the long run, it won't matter so much.  But since you aren't twinking, the better stats from the getgo would be more beneficial to you.</P><P>I won't comment on servers.  IMO, they are basically all the same.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
