		<hr size="1">PvP bards spends a lot of time running, but they can be deadly as they are next to impossible to hurt.  out of range, mega resist songs (just an idea with my drum by the time i was low 40s and got one of the better resist songs i was able to sing that and push my MR, FR, CR close to 200.  my normal resists are in the 40-60 range.  now add some resist gear in there and ill max out those 3 with 1 song, that still leaves 3 more songs to fight with)  nice DoTs that are also debuffs, mez, charm pets, stun, mana tap, ok heals, you name it they have it.</P><P>a bard can be almost impossible to kill 1 on 1 in an open area.  there melee sucks big time so dont go there even with slow and haste you will be nothing compaired even to a warrior who has umong the lowest DPS on the tanks.</P><P>as for race,  nos has it about right.</P><P>half elf = 2 places to start so that helps.  bad eyes, but better then human, ok base stats, ok base skills.  hide, forage IIRC.</P><P>vah shir = 1 starting place with very safe newbie zone.  ok newbie armor, but next to impossible to get by the time the armor is useful.  in other words by the time you finish all the quests and kill all the mobs to get your armor you will be in your 20s and will have way outgrown your newbie armor.  do the newbie drum quest though for the vah shir.  its a nice drum with 2AC.  very hard to find a drum at low levels that has AC on it.</P><P>nice starting stats (best CHA IIRC), high STA, STR, AGI, DEX, but low INT.  safefall, forage, sneak, hide all for being a kat.  big draw back is their size.  they are as big as barbarians so are on the large armor size chart, and do not fit in any of the elf door ways.  well most of them at least.  example you can not get into the bank in kelethin you are to big.</P><P>my bard = 55 vah shir and i love it.  not many vah shir bards on my server vs half elf.</P><P>one huge advantage the half elf has is they can use any of the human, wood elf, high elf, or dark elf, cultur armor and if they chose Rallos Zek as their god, then they can get some extreemly nice armor without getting into elemental levels or months of work in Nro LDoN.</P><P>good luck, enjoy and visit <A HREF="HTTP://www.eqdiva.com" TARGET="_BLANK">www.eqdiva.com</A> for some of the best bard advice you can find any place on the web.</P><P><hr><font style=font-size:8pt color=yellow>*Worlds worst speller*<BR><font color=yellow><BR>"For those who believe, then no proof is needed.  For those who are skeptics, then no proof will suffice."<font color=00FFFF><BR>"Pigs get fat, but Hogs get slaughtered and VI is a big HOG."<BR><font color=yellow> "So, reading some of my posts is sort of like having sex in your parents house???"  Dr. Zin</P><P></font><BR><br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
