		<hr size="1">Most of the bards on my server are male elves of some sort, they all tend to look alike to me.  I've seen exactly two other Vah Shir bards so far, one male, one female, it's very rare to see the Muse tag over someone's head.  I play a Vah Shir bard, I liked the starting stats and like I said.  For reasons stated by others, other races have their own advantages and disadvantages.</P><P>Bards are amazing in PvP.  Melee damage isn't great but it's not bad either. Speed, nukes, slows, stuns, dots, and high resists all make for a nsty PvP experience and if you belong to the Fansy camp, it's incredibly easy for a bard to 'recruit' some help from npc's.  At higher levels, talking AA's here, bard's can instantly lose agro from all mobs chasing them... I'm not a big fan of killing people with trains but bards at higher levels are as good or better at it than monks even.</P><P>For me, getting through the 50's and 60's was easier with my bard than with any other class I've played.  From a very early age bards can take down red and yellow con mobs consistantly and really, unless it summons, roots or snares it can't kill you, well, unless it can kill you with a single blow.  A well played bard rarely dies to mobs that can't do one or more of the above and they're masters of the joust.</P><P>There are a few people here who play PvP almost exclusively and can provide better tips than I can, also <A HREF="HTTP://www.eqdiva.com" TARGET="_BLANK">www.eqdiva.com</A> has a good pvp forum.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
